# HTML Conventions

## Lucide Icons

This project uses [Lucide](https://lucide.dev) loaded via CDN. Icons are rendered with `<i>` tags and initialized by calling `lucide.createIcons()` once at the bottom of `<body>`.

```html
<!-- ✅ GOOD — use data-lucide attribute -->
<i data-lucide="download"></i>
<i data-lucide="terminal-square"></i>

<!-- ❌ BAD — do not use emoji, image tags, or SVG inline for icons -->
<img src="icon.svg" alt="download">
⬇️
```

Always call `lucide.createIcons()` after the scripts load:

```html
<script src="https://unpkg.com/lucide@latest"></script>
<!-- ... other scripts ... -->
<script>
    lucide.createIcons();
</script>
</body>
```

## Semantic Structure

- Use `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>` — avoid generic `<div>` wrappers for top-level layout
- Each `<section>` should have a meaningful `id` for anchor navigation (e.g., `id="features"`)
- Buttons that trigger JS actions use `<button>`; navigation links use `<a href="#">`

## Attribute Order

Prefer: `class` → `id` → `data-*` → event handlers
